snippet.textDisplay:
When Unai Emery first came to Arsenal (which was just less than two years), everyone .. The "fans" .. They claimed that Unai was THE ONE. When people saw his training sessions (where he wanted pressing .. But, some of the highly paid players either DIDN'T WANT TO or did it HALF - HEARTEDLY), people were excited and hoped Arsenal would play with more passion and intensity. But, the players LET HIM DOWN. What happened after a few "bad" results? The "fans" demanded for Unai to be sacked. And they wanted Mesut Ozeil back into the team.
Well .. Did that helped?? No.
Because Unai was not the "problem". And Ozeil, despite his technical ability, is not aggressive enough for the EPL (and it doesn't help that he does not like tracking back) and is usually a "passenger" when he is picked to play. When are the PLAYERS GOING TO BE ACCOUNTABLE?
So now, Mikel Arteta is back. Great. But, what happens when the "bad" results come? Or he doesn't pick certain "popular" players? Will the "fans" ask for Arteta to be sacked? The fickleness of the sport and some "fans."
